TheÂ 2022 Beijing Winter Olympics are just around the corner and many Chinese are excited as it will make Beijing the first city in history to host both a Summer and Winter Olympics. What are the big events to watch for? How are the athletes feeling? And how is China handling the COVID-19 pandemic to ensure a successful Olympic Games? To find out more, we've invited guests who have been highly involved in the Olympics in the past. They are Meagan Duhamel, Olympic Winter Games gold medalist; Peter Mennel, Secretary General of the Austrian Olympic Committee; Esko Aho, former Prime Minister of Finland; and Claude Stricker, executive director of International Academy of Sport Science and Technology, or AISTS.